verses.text: In that day shall this song be sung in the land of Judah ; We have a strong city ; salvation will \add God\add* appoint \add for\add* walls and bulwarks.
Open ye the gates , that the righteous nation which keepeth the truth may enter in.\f + \fr 26.2 \ft truth: Heb. truths\f*

Thou wilt keep \add him\add* in perfect peace , \add whose\add* mind \add is\add* stayed \add on thee:\add* because he trusteth in thee.\f + \fr 26.3 \ft perfect…: Heb. peace, peace\f*\f + \fr 26.3 \ft mind: or, thought, or, imagination\f*

Trust ye in the

d* for ever : for in the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3050"\+w*
d* 
d \+w JEHOVAH|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* \add is\add* everlasting strength :  +  r 26.4  t everlasting…: Heb. the rock of ages * \p
¶ For he bringeth down them that dwell on high ; the lofty city , he layeth it low ; he layeth it low , \add even\add* to the ground ; he bringeth it \add even\add* to the dust.
The foot shall tread it down , \add even\add* the feet of the poor , \add and\add* the steps of the needy.
The way of the just \add is\add* uprightness : thou, most upright , dost weigh the path of the just.
Yea, in the way of thy judgments , O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, have we waited for thee; the desire of \add our\add* soul \add is\add* to thy name , and to the remembrance of thee.

With my soul have I desired thee in the night ; yea, with my spirit within me will I seek thee early : for when thy judgments \add are\add* in the earth , the inhabitants of the world will learn righteousness.

Let favour be shewed to the wicked , \add yet\add* will he not learn righteousness : in the land of uprightness will he deal unjustly , and will not behold the majesty of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.

\nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, \add when\add* thy hand is lifted up , they will not see : \add but\add* they shall see , and be ashamed for \add their\add* envy at the people ; yea, the fire of thine enemies shall devour them.\f + \fr 26.11 \ft at…: or, toward thy people\f* \p
¶ \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, thou wilt ordain peace for us: for thou also hast wrought all our works in us.\f + \fr 26.12 \ft in us: or, for us\f*
O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our God , \add other\add* lords beside thee have had dominion over us: \add but\add* by thee only will we make mention of thy name.
\add They are\add* dead , they shall not live ; \add they are\add* deceased , they shall not rise : therefore hast thou visited and destroyed them, and made all their memory to perish.

Thou hast increased the nation , O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, thou hast increased the nation : thou art glorified : thou hadst removed \add it\add* far \add unto\add* all the ends of the earth.
\nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, in trouble have they visited thee, they poured out a prayer \add when\add* thy chastening \add was\add* upon them.\f + \fr 26.16 \ft prayer: Heb. secret speech\f*

Like as a woman with child , \add that\add* draweth near the time of her delivery , is in pain , \add and\add* crieth out in her pangs ; so have we been in thy sight , O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.
We have been with child , we have been in pain , we have as it were brought forth wind ; we have not wrought any deliverance in the earth ; neither have the inhabitants of the world fallen.

Thy dead \add men\add* shall live , \add together with\add* my dead body shall they arise. Awake and sing , ye that dwell in dust : for thy dew \add is as\add* the dew of herbs , and the earth shall cast out the dead. \p
¶ Come , my people , enter thou into thy chambers , and shut thy doors about thee: hide thyself as it were for a little moment , until the indignation be overpast.

For, behold, the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* cometh out of his place to punish the inhabitants of the earth for their iniquity : the earth also shall disclose her blood , and shall no more cover her slain.\f + \fr 26.21 \ft blood: Heb. bloods\f*
